messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I need you to please send a fire ambulance.
I need you to please come.
My brother's drunk and he took out a knife. Please come now.
Has he cut anybody, Ma'am?
He's threatening and he touched a 12-year-old. Please come now.
I am sending someone. Ma'am, How old is your brother?
He's forty-three, and he's been drinking.
Ma'am, you said he's been drinking. What has he been drinking?
Yes, he has. Has he cut anybody yet? Is he threatening anyone?
I'm sending someone right now, what's your name?
I'm telling you he's yelling.
Okay, what's your name?
Manny
What is it?
Manny, Manny, Manny. Please come.
Okay, just stay on the phone with me, okay?
Yes, you did. Unless she's lying. She doesn't know you.
Ma'am, why would she lie?
I don't know it. I don't know it.
What's your brother's name?
Manny
Spell it for me.
M-A-N-N-Y
Manny, Okay. Is he on any type of medication?
Yes, but I don't know what. I don't care.
Does he have a history of doing this?
Yes, that's why his children were taken away.
Has he ever hurt anyone before?
He says that on June 16, he's going to die, and I think he wants to take us with him.
I don't hear him anymore. Is he... Hold on.
Hold on.
Okay.
Look at his wife.
Okay, no problem. Hold on.
Hold on.
Mm-hmm. You go ahead.
He's talking to her on the phone. He's talking to the woman that left.
Does he still have a knife in his hand?
No, I can't see it. He's locked up in the room.
Mommy, go there. Open the door.
Okay, ma'am, it looks like I've got an officer that should be there.
Ma'am, did he put the knife back?
Ma'am.
Is that a gun?
Yeah, but he doesn't have a gun.
Are you with the officer now?
He's somebody to talk to him. No, put it back.
Are you with the officer, ma'am?
Oh, excuse me. I was just trying to be...
Ma'am, is that the officer?
Thank you, sir.
